cs.CG, cs.GR, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the library manipulates ensembles of cycles (quadrics) in spaces of arbitrary dimensionality and metrics, which involves geometric computations. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the library can produce illustrations and animations in the two-dimensional case. 
- cs.SD (Symbolic Data) is another possibility as the library operates with both numeric and symbolic data of cycles. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a relevant category as the library likely involves data structures and algorithms for manipulating ensembles of cycles. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is also a possibility as the library uses the Ginac library for symbolic computations.
